## Test Run 2: Incremental Processing (2 newly classified emails)

**Purpose:** Verify that the workflow only picks up NEW classified emails
and does not reprocess emails already marked "Draft Generated."

**Setup:** Manually changed Status of two previously unclassified emails
(test@example.com and student@example.com) to "Classified" and assigned
Category and Urgency values.

**Result:** Workflow executed successfully, processing only 2 new emails.

| Draft ID | Linked Email | Draft Preview | Status |
|----------|-------------|---------------|--------|
| 12 | test@example.com | "I'd be happy to help with y..." | NEEDS_REVIEW |
| 13 | student@example.com | "To reset your password, ple..." | NEEDS_REVIEW |

### Key Observation

The workflow correctly ignored the 11 emails already marked "Draft
Generated" and processed only the 2 newly classified emails. This
confirms the status-based filtering and update mechanism prevents
duplicate processing. ✅

## Known Issue: NO_DRAFT_NEEDED Rows

Three rows (Draft IDs 5, 8, 10) contain the sentinel string
`NO_DRAFT_NEEDED` in the Draft Body field. These should have been
filtered out by the IF node but were written to the table, likely
due to trailing whitespace or newline characters in the Flowise
response causing the exact-string comparison to fail.

**Impact:** Minor — these rows are easily identified and can be
filtered out in dashboard views or manually removed.

**Recommended fix:** Change the IF node condition from "is not equal
to" to "does not contain" for more robust matching.

